  "text": "Based on the success of modeling around-corner propagation along hallways inside buildings [CITATION_1] , we propose two theory-inspired empirical models, namely, a single-slope scattering inspired model [CITATION_2] where the corner is treated as a new source, and a single-slope diffraction inspired model where edgediffraction around the corner is assumed to be the dominant mechanism. Let x be the unwrapped distance, aka the \"Manhattan distance\", between the two terminals, and without loss of generality assuming one terminal is fixed, and the other terminal moves away along the street and then turns into a perpendicular street. As distance x increases, the propagation channel changes from same-street to around-corner. The diffraction inspired model is given by",
